Translated_Comment:
Some Indian media outlets like this one, have been spreading exaggerated and fear-inducing reports about the spread of Human Meta pneumococcus virus (HMPV). However, there is no sign of any emergency or widespread concern here in China. People are going about their daily lives as usual. Therefore, such reports should not be believed without proper verification.

HMPV is not a new virus, nor has it recently originated in China. This virus was first identified in 2001 and is commonly found across the world, especially during the winter season. It primarily affects young children and the elderly, causing mild symptoms such as fever, cough, and respiratory issues. Severe health complications are extremely rare.

Some Indian media outlets are portraying this as a new epidemic in China, which creates unnecessary panic and spreads misinformation.

It is important not to fall prey to such sensational news. Instead, rely only on credible sources such as official health departments in China or the World Health Organization (WHO) for accurate information. Ignore false narratives, focus on verified facts, and remain calm. 

From: Jay KV, Nanjing. China
